						<summary>

						<p>In the same place on the hill.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Undated. In <hi rend="italic">Vaṭṭeḻuttu</hi> characters. (8th cent. A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that the image was that of the Jaina monk, Māgaṇandi, a disciple of Ashṭa-upavāsi Bhaṭārar, a monk of the big monastery called Perumpaḷḷi in Parāntakaparvatham <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Kuṟaṇḍi, a village in Veṇbu-nāḍu, and the <hi rend="italic">Nāṭṭār</hi> of the Nāṭṭāṟṟuppuram, caused the image to be carved out.</p>						

						</summary>
